Narrative: The vehicle was traveling with ADS engaged westbound on [XXX] in the right lane near [XXX]. [REDACTED, MAY CONTAIN CONFIDENTIAL BUSINESS INFORMATION] After the driver disengaged the ADS, the truck straddled the object, with its tires passing to each side. The object made contact with cap of the transmission air tank and pulled the cap off. The air in the tank was released and the driver pulled onto the shoulder and stopped to assess the situation. A vendor replaced the cap and the truck returned to the home terminal as planned. The cap to the air tank was the only damage resulting from the incident. No other vehicles were involved. The features of the ADS that were engaged just prior to the incident were: Adaptive Cruise Control, Lane Keep, Lane change and Ending Lanes. For details and data, see Torc Robotics report submission number 30330-3561-1. Data Availability, Other: ADS related.

The vehicle was traveling with ADS engaged eastbound on [XXX] in the second lane from the left near [XXX]. [REDACTED, MAY CONTAIN CONFIDENTIAL BUSINESS INFORMATION] After the driver disengaged the ADS, the truck's
passenger side steer tire rolled over the object and the object punctured the passenger side fuel tank. Fuel began to leak from the tank
and the driver pulled onto the shoulder and stopped to assess the situation. The NM State Police arrived on the scene and the truck was
towed to a secure location. The NM DOT performed the initial cleanup of the fuel at the scene and a vendor was secured by the operator
to complete the cleanup process. Damage to the fuel tank was the only damage resulting from the incident. No other vehicles were
involved.
The features of the ADS that were engaged just prior to the incident were: Adaptive Cruise Control, Lane Keep, Lane change and Ending
Lanes.
Data Availability, Other: ADS related data
